@startuml RepositoryArchitecture_Abstract
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 80
skinparam ranksep 60
skinparam linetype ortho

title Repository Architecture — Abstract Interfaces

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' PUBLIC SURFACE
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

class Repository <<facade>> #FFFDE7 {
  +save(data, hint?) : dict
  +fetch(Query) : ResultSet
  __
  +add_pre_transform(fn)
  +add_post_transform(fn)
}
note top of Repository
  Acquired from a connection string.
  Internally resolves one StorageStrategy.
  User only calls save() / fetch().
end note

class Query <<builder>> #FFFDE7 {
  +select(cols) : self
  +from_table(table) : self
  +where(clause, param) : self
  +limit(n) : self
  +build() : Query
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' EXTRACTION — Python data → abstract View  (compile-time, template)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

abstract class ExtractionPolicy <<policy>> #E8F5E9 {
  +{static} detect(data) : ExtractionPolicy
  +{abstract} extract(data) : View
}
note bottom of ExtractionPolicy
  **How** Python data becomes C++ View.

  1. Auto-detect format (one type check)
     or skip via caller hint.
  2. Tag-dispatch to compile-time optimized
     extractor (Polars, Pandas, Arrow, dict…).
  3. Returns a thin **View** that
     StorageStrategy consumes.
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' VIEW — the universal interchange between extraction and storage
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

abstract class View <<interface>> #E0F2F1 {
  +{abstract} schema() : Schema
  +{abstract} num_rows() : size_t
}

class ArrowView <<view>> #E0F2F1 {
  RecordBatchReader handle
}

class RowView <<view>> #E0F2F1 {
  single RowMap
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' STORAGE — where data lives  (runtime, virtual — one per repo)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

abstract class StorageStrategy <<interface>> #E8F5E9 {
  +{abstract} capabilities() : Capabilities
  __
  +fetch(query) : ResultSet
  +persist(View)
  +save(key, RowMap)
}
note bottom of StorageStrategy
  **Where** data lives.
  Resolved from connection string.
  One concrete instance per Repository.

  **Transpose is internal.**
  Column→row transposition for bulk DB
  write is owned by the strategy, not
  exposed. Uses `if constexpr` trampoline
  with Simd enum {Scalar, Avx2, ...} —
  zero per-row overhead, fully inlined.
end note

class Capabilities <<value>> #E8F5E9 {
  +can_fetch : bool
  +can_persist : bool
  +can_save : bool
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' VALUE TYPES
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

together {
  class CellValue <<variant>> #F3E5F5 {
    Null | bool | int64 | double | string
  }

  class RowMap <<alias>> #F3E5F5 {
    map<string, CellValue>
  }

  class ResultSet <<value>> #F3E5F5 {
    +columns : string[]
    +rows : CellValue[][]
  }
}

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' SIMD DISPATCH  (internal to StorageStrategy, compile-time)
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

enum Simd <<enum>> #FFF3E0 {
  Scalar
  Avx2
  /Neon  (future)/
  /Avx512 (future)/
}
note right of Simd
  Detected once at module init
  via `cpu_supports_avx2()`.
  Pipeline is templated on Simd —
  `if constexpr` compiles away
  unused branches.
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' RELATIONSHIPS
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Repository *-down- "1" StorageStrategy : owns (from conn string)
Repository ..> Query : accepts
Repository ..> ExtractionPolicy : data → View

ExtractionPolicy ..> View : produces
ArrowView -up-|> View
RowView -up-|> View

StorageStrategy ..> View : consumes
StorageStrategy ..> Capabilities : declares
StorageStrategy ..> Simd : dispatches internally
StorageStrategy ..> RowMap : reads / writes

Repository ..> ResultSet : returns

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' NOTES
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note as N_pipeline
  **Pipeline (internal to StorageStrategy):**

  View → partition rows → transpose<Simd>
  → BCP buffer → ODBC driver → DB

  Multi-threaded: N reader/transpose threads
  feed M writer connections via lock-free queue.
  GIL released for entire pipeline.
end note

N_pipeline .. StorageStrategy

@enduml
